-- McLaren’s Hamilton Wins Pole Position for Brazilian Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-11-24T17:36:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-24/mclaren-s-hamilton-wins-pole-position-for-brazilian-grand-prix.html
Lewis Hamilton won pole position for
tomorrow’s Brazilian Grand Prix, the final race of the Formula
One season.  Hamilton posted a time of 1 minute, 12.458 seconds around
the Interlagos circuit in Sao Paulo for his series-best seventh
pole of the season. Jenson Button, Hamilton’s McLaren teammate,
qualified second ahead of Red Bull’s Mark Webber.  Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel will start fourth on the grid
as he seeks his third consecutive world championship. The 25-
year-old German leads Ferrari’s Fernando Alonso, who qualfied
eighth, by 13 points in the standings with a victory tomorrow
worth 25 points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  